## Deployment

### Docker Compose (MVP)

```yaml
services:
  voice-runtime:
    build: ./backend
    ports:
      - "8000:8000"
    depends_on:
      - postgres
      - redis
    environment:
      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://user:pass@postgres:5432/voiceai
      REDIS_URL: redis://redis:6379/0

  postgres:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    volumes:
      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine

volumes:
  pgdata:
```

### Dockerfile Best Practices

- Multi-stage build (builder + runtime)
- Use `uv` for dependency installation in Docker
- Non-root user
- Health check endpoint

```dockerfile
FROM python:3.12-slim AS builder
COPY --from=ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:latest /uv /usr/local/bin/uv
WORKDIR /app
COPY pyproject.toml uv.lock ./
RUN uv sync --frozen --no-dev

FROM python:3.12-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /app/.venv .venv
COPY src/ src/
CMD [".venv/bin/uvicorn", "src.main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]
```

This document serves as the foundation for maintaining code quality, consistency, and low-latency performance across the Voice AI Runtime backend.
